    "It achieved an average AUPR of 0.70 and 0.89, as well as F max scores of 0.80 and 0.88, for GO terms and EC numbers, respectively (Fig. 3).",
    "Moreover, it consistently maintained strong performance, with average AUPR scores of 0.64, 0.65, and 0.80, alongside corresponding F max values of 0.82, 0.75, and 0.81, for the three branches of GO terms -CC, BP, and MF (Fig. 3d).",
    "Overall, PhiGnet significantly outperformed all supervised and unsupervised approaches across the benchmark datasets.",
